The paper discusses fog computing, which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC) that focuses on bringing computation closer to the edge devices. The paper also mentions software-defined networking (SDN) and network function virtualization (NFV), which are subfields of computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed middleware is service-oriented, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions QoS management and dynamic adaptability, which are topics in control systems (cs.SY) and architecture (cs.AR).
